name: Inland Valley Hope Partners
review_text: Wouldn't help because I had a service dog, on disability, not an addict or mentally ill, discrimination at it's worst! What's next, i'm white? I'm homeless & normal people need help too!!

name: Inland Valley Hope Partners
review_text: I was told by Kevin that the voucher program was discontinued but he had one more Leftwich was supposed to be for me, well kevin said he would email the voucher on Monday which I never got and going to his office to pickup the voucher was to no avail, he was in a meeting and nobody in the office knew anything about a voucher except the program is discontinued.  I left several messages for Kevin which he never returned,  this meant I would be on the streets which I've never experienced before but with the help of God I was not put thru that. Kevin people depend on you to be a man of your word, the least you could have done us leave the voucher with the receptionist if there ever was a voucher.  You don't know how hard it was for me to get to that office and you not being there

name: Inland Valley Hope Partners
review_text: What a wonderful organization!!! Miss Karen is the Best!!!

name: Inland Valley Hope Partners
review_text:
This is a place where you trust,  it's clean,  they provide ensuing for you,
so you can focus on your journey,  the staff is there to help you succeed if you want it. Any time you live with others,  there will be drama,  but if you know how to stay out of it,  you will be fine.  Great place to live.

name: Inland Valley Hope Partners
review_text: Super group of kind-hearted heroes. We were able to acquire some food & hygiene kits with no problem at all. They had clothes to offer as well, if y'all be cold or lacking in that department. Sweet peeps helping those in need. Much appreciated!
